WEBVTT

00:05.705 --> 00:08.050
Narrator:
In New York City war on crime,

00:08.074 --> 00:11.682
the worst criminal offenders
are pursued by the detectives

00:11.712 --> 00:13.385
of the Major Case Squad.

00:13.413 --> 00:15.324
These are their stories.

00:16.950 --> 00:19.396
For years, he went to the gym
every evening at 7:00.

00:19.419 --> 00:21.660
Two weeks ago, he started
going in the morning.

00:21.688 --> 00:23.429
- It's no problem.
- Hello, Jack.

00:23.457 --> 00:25.960
- Hey, how are you?
- Do you have to do that?

00:25.993 --> 00:28.667
- ( cell phone ringing )
- Relax. That's me.

00:28.695 --> 00:30.231
I'll be right back.

00:32.533 --> 00:34.171
Yes?

00:34.201 --> 00:36.681
I was just thinking about you.

00:36.703 --> 00:38.512
You're welcome.

00:38.539 --> 00:40.519
I remembered you liked tulips,

00:40.541 --> 00:42.350
so I thought--

00:42.376 --> 00:45.186
yes, yes, that'll be fine.

00:45.212 --> 00:47.692
It's Part 42, Judge Ross.

00:47.714 --> 00:49.387
I'll see you there.

00:55.389 --> 00:57.369
Man #1 on tape: Do you have to do that?

00:57.391 --> 00:59.234
Man #2 on tape: Relax.

01:01.028 --> 01:04.474
Mr. Keefer waited till his victim
reached a deserted part of 2nd Avenue

01:04.498 --> 01:05.977
before striking her.

01:05.999 --> 01:08.639
He then ran into the subway,
and got rid of his coat and hat.

01:08.669 --> 01:10.478
When he was stopped by the police,

01:10.504 --> 01:12.313
he gave a false name and address.

01:12.339 --> 01:14.979
What, if anything, did you
conclude from this behavior?

01:15.008 --> 01:17.488
He attacked his victim not
because of some delusion,

01:17.511 --> 01:20.651
but because she rejected
his advances at work.

01:20.681 --> 01:24.652
In those respects, he does not
meet the criteria for a plea

01:24.685 --> 01:28.428
of not guilty by reason
of mental disease or defect.

01:28.455 --> 01:30.332
Thank you, Doctor.

01:30.357 --> 01:32.166
Judge: Thank you, Mr. Carver.

01:32.192 --> 01:35.332
Before cross-examination
of the expert witness,

01:35.362 --> 01:37.672
the Court calls a 15 minute recess.

01:37.698 --> 01:40.338
It meant a lot to me
you were there this afternoon.

01:40.367 --> 01:42.506
I know you had to rush, and don't worry,

01:42.536 --> 01:44.516
I'll take care of that traffic ticket.

01:44.538 --> 01:47.178
Thank you. That's very sweet of you.

01:47.207 --> 01:49.517
About Saturday, if you can't--

01:49.543 --> 01:52.183
No, no, no. I cleared my schedule.

01:52.212 --> 01:54.192
Thank you.

01:54.214 --> 01:56.717
She really needs to talk to someone.

01:58.051 --> 02:00.031
Here. No, thanks.

02:00.053 --> 02:01.794
Hmm? Thank you.

02:01.822 --> 02:03.802
I have to drive home.

02:03.824 --> 02:06.134
Sara, listen, as part of my per diem,

02:06.159 --> 02:08.469
the DA got me a suite here tonight.

02:08.495 --> 02:10.668
We could finish this bottle up there.

02:12.666 --> 02:14.976
That's a very tempting offer.

02:15.002 --> 02:16.845
Please say yes.

02:19.339 --> 02:21.979
It's too soon, Charles.

02:22.009 --> 02:24.319
I hope you understand.

02:24.344 --> 02:26.324
Sure. Sure.

02:26.346 --> 02:28.485
Everything in good time.

02:28.515 --> 02:30.256
( applauding )

02:30.283 --> 02:34.561
Thank you so much for coming
on this very special day for Ricky.

02:35.589 --> 02:38.069
So much has happened these last few months,

02:38.091 --> 02:41.004
but Richard has acted like
a man and I am very,

02:41.028 --> 02:42.837
very proud of him.

02:42.863 --> 02:44.843
Seeing him grow up like this,

02:44.865 --> 02:48.210
I just wish his sister Sophie would stay a
little girl forever.

02:48.235 --> 02:50.010
( crowd "awws")

02:50.037 --> 02:52.347
Everybody, this is-- this is Lauren.

02:52.372 --> 02:54.283
Hi, honey!

02:54.307 --> 02:56.878
Well, thank you, and enjoy yourselves.

02:56.910 --> 02:58.446
( applauding )

03:03.583 --> 03:05.119
Hi.

03:05.152 --> 03:07.496
How he dares invite that bimbo...

03:09.156 --> 03:12.365
I'm sorry, Julie, he just makes me so mad.

03:13.994 --> 03:16.338
- Sara.
- Charles.

03:17.497 --> 03:19.636
This is my sister Julie.

03:19.666 --> 03:21.976
And this is Sophie. This is Dr. Webb.

03:22.002 --> 03:24.642
Charlie'll do. And how are you, Sophie?

03:24.671 --> 03:26.981
- Good.
- Why don't we all sit over there?

03:27.007 --> 03:29.487
- You know, I don't know.
- It can only help.

03:29.509 --> 03:31.318
Sara, you can't force these things.

03:31.344 --> 03:33.915
- Whenever you're ready.
- She's ready now.

